id1 = kernel32_idb.id1
segments = id1.segments
assert len(segments) == 2
for segment in segments:
    assert segment.bounds.start < segment.bounds.end
assert segments[0].bounds.start == 1754271744
assert segments[1].bounds.start == 1755172864
assert id1.get_segment(1754271744).bounds.start == 1754271744
assert id1.get_segment(1754271745).bounds.start == 1754271744
assert id1.get_segment(1755168768 - 1).bounds.start == 1754271744
assert id1.get_next_segment(1754271744).bounds.start == 1755172864
assert id1.get_flags(1754271744) == 9616
kern32_test([(695, 32, None), (695, 64, None), (700, 32, None), (700, 64,
    None)])
